// CDNS file - CMFT Directive NameSpace file
// Tells the extension that these exist - and tells Project: Reassembly what's valid where (wip).
// P:R should do a static check on the directives to see if they all exist, and report unknown ones.
// This file can be imported to use these namespaced directives.
* <time> [number]
  "Sustains this line for a certain amount of time, specified in frames (60fps). A base value of 60 is added to this for fade time."
* <rtime> [number] "Sustains this line for a certain amount of time, specified in frames (60fps). Also removes fade time."
* <wait> [number] "Blanks the screen for a certain amount of time, specified in frames (60fps)."
* <command> "Executes the handler's `command` function with this line's unformatted text as its argument."
* <cut> "Marks this text as having no fade time."